Three of the seven aspects of organizational culture are as follows: This component relates to the extent to which workers are encouraged and permitted to be innovative and take chances in their job. Google, a corporation recognized for its creative culture and willingness to take chances and try new things, is an example of this dimension. Attention to detail: The degree to which personnel are required to pay attention to details and maintain high standards of correctness in their job is referred to as this dimension. Mercedes-Benz is an example of a corporation that demonstrates this dimension, since it is recognized for its emphasis on accuracy and quality in the construction of its automobiles. Outcome orientation: This factor relates to how much emphasis the organization places on accomplishing particular objectives and outcomes opposed than just following a set of procedures. Amazon is an example of a corporation that demonstrates this characteristic, since it is recognized for its great attention on customer pleasure and quantitative results. 